Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @21 Day Aged British Rump Steaks{2} from your fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{160%g} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

While the corn chars, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%g}.

Finely chop the @Chives{1%bunch}(finely chopped) (use scissors if easier).

In a large #bowl{}, mix together the @Mayonnaise{64%g}, @Coleslaw Mix{120%g} and half the chives. When the corn is charred, stir it into the slaw and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan.

When the chips have 15 mins remaining, return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Season the steaks with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Rump steaks naturally vary in shape, so adjust the following timings depending on how you like yours cooked.

Once very hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned and medium-rare, about ~{5%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Cook each side for 1 min more if you like it more well done.

Once cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The steak is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

When the chips have 5 mins remaining, sprinkle over the cheese, then return to the oven for the remaining cook time.

Meanwhile, while the steaks are resting, clean the frying pan, then return to medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Chipotle Paste{20%g} and fry for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @Water for the Sauce{75%ml} and @Honey{15%g}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for 1 min to loosen.

Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir the @Unsalted Butter{20%g} into the sauce until melted.

When everything's ready, transfer the steaks to your #plate{} and spoon over the chipotle honey butter sauce.

Serve the charred corn slaw and cheesy chips alongside.

Drizzle the @Burger Sauce{45%g} over the chips and finish by sprinkling over the remaining chives.

Enjoy!